---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Course Creators"
  description="Build and publish courses using the course.yaml manifest — from directory layout to question banks, assignments, and the PR workflow."
  chapterId="creators"
>
  <nav slot="toc">
    <a href="#layout"        class="docs-toc-link">Course Layout</a>
    <a href="#yaml-format"   class="docs-toc-link">course.yaml Format</a>
    <a href="#sections"      class="docs-toc-link">YAML Sections</a>
    <a href="#questions"     class="docs-toc-link">Question Types</a>
    <a href="#solutions"     class="docs-toc-link">solutions.yaml</a>
    <a href="#assets"        class="docs-toc-link">Assets</a>
    <a href="#pr-workflow"   class="docs-toc-link">PR Workflow</a>
    <a href="#checklist"     class="docs-toc-link">Checklist</a>
  </nav>

  <section id="layout" class="docs-section">
    <h2 class="docs-section-title">
      Course Directory Layout
      <span class="docs-section-badge" style="background:color-mix(in srgb,#a78bfa 12%,transparent);color:#a78bfa;border:1px solid color-mix(in srgb,#a78bfa 30%,transparent)">Setup</span>
    </h2>
    <p>Every course lives under <code>engine/courses/&#123;slug&#125;/</code>. Copy the template to start:</p>
    <div class="docs-pre">
      <div class="docs-pre__bar"><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__lang">bash</span></div>
      <code>cp -r engine/courses/template engine/courses/your-slug</code>
    </div>
    <p>Full directory structure:</p>
    <div class="docs-pre">
      <div class="docs-pre__bar"><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__lang">tree</span></div>
      <code>engine/courses/your-slug/
├── course.yaml              ← single source of truth (edit this)
├── solutions.yaml           ← all answers (NEVER commit to main — private only)
├── course.json              ← auto-generated on publish (do not edit)
├── contributors.json        ← auto-generated on publish (do not edit)
└── assets/
    ├── images/              (thumbnail + banner + og + badge)
    │   ├── thumbnail.png    (16:9, min 800×450px)
    │   ├── banner.png       (3:1, min 1200×400px)
    │   ├── og.png           (1200×630px, for social sharing)
    │   └── badge.png        (completion badge, square)
    ├── code/                (runnable code examples, by chapter)
    │   └── ch01/
    │       └── example.js
    └── docs/                (PDFs, cheatsheets, assignment briefs)
        ├── ch01-assignment.pdf
        └── final-project-brief.pdf</code>
    </div>
    <div class="docs-callout docs-callout--danger">
      <span class="docs-callout__icon">🔒</span>
      <div class="docs-callout__body"><strong>Never commit <code>solutions.yaml</code> to the main branch.</strong> Add it to <code>.gitignore</code>, keep it on a private branch, or store it encrypted. The grader reads question IDs from <code>course.yaml</code> and matches them to answers in <code>solutions.yaml</code> at runtime.</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="yaml-format" class="docs-section">
    <h2 class="docs-section-title">course.yaml — Pure YAML Format</h2>
    <p><code>course.yaml</code> is a pure YAML file — no Markdown frontmatter, no mixed formats. Every field is machine-readable and validated by <code>validate-pr.yml</code> on PR open. The parser (<code>engine/lib/course-parser.ts</code>) reads it directly via <code>js-yaml</code>.</p>

    <div class="docs-callout docs-callout--tip">
      <span class="docs-callout__icon">💡</span>
      <div class="docs-callout__body">Validate locally before opening a PR: <code>python -c "import yaml,sys; yaml.safe_load(sys.stdin)" &lt; course.yaml</code> — any YAML error is reported immediately.</div>
    </div>

    <p>The file has 18 top-level sections in a fixed order:</p>
    <div class="docs-table-wrap">
      <table class="docs-table">
        <thead><tr><th>#</th><th>Section key</th><th>Required</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>1</td><td><code>metadata</code></td><td>✓</td><td>ID, version, status, visibility, dates, language</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2</td><td><code>identity</code></td><td>✓</td><td>Title, tagline, short/full description, cover images, brand colours</td></tr>
          <tr><td>3</td><td><code>classification</code></td><td>✓</td><td>Track (category), level, tags, topics, target audience, skills gained</td></tr>
          <tr><td>4</td><td><code>effort</code></td><td>✓</td><td>Video / reading / exercise hours, pace, weekly commitment</td></tr>
          <tr><td>5</td><td><code>people</code></td><td>✓</td><td>Curator, contributors, reviewers with GitHub usernames</td></tr>
          <tr><td>6</td><td><code>credits</code></td><td>✓</td><td>Full attribution for every external resource used anywhere in the course</td></tr>
          <tr><td>7</td><td><code>prerequisites</code></td><td></td><td>Required knowledge, prerequisite courses, tools, accounts</td></tr>
          <tr><td>8</td><td><code>outcomes</code></td><td></td><td>What students can do after completion, broken down per chapter</td></tr>
          <tr><td>9</td><td><code>curriculum</code></td><td>✓</td><td>All chapters, sections, subsections, and lessons with content</td></tr>
          <tr><td>10</td><td><code>chapter_tests</code></td><td>✓</td><td>Assessment questions for each chapter (no answers — those are in solutions.yaml)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>11</td><td><code>chapter_assignments</code></td><td></td><td>Coding assignments per chapter with rubric and review settings</td></tr>
          <tr><td>12</td><td><code>final_test</code></td><td></td><td>Comprehensive final test spanning all chapters</td></tr>
          <tr><td>13</td><td><code>final_assignment</code></td><td></td><td>Capstone project (unlocked by final test)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>14</td><td><code>certificate</code></td><td>✓</td><td>Certificate requirements, badge, and template settings</td></tr>
          <tr><td>15</td><td><code>assets</code></td><td></td><td>Manifest of all asset files referenced in the course</td></tr>
          <tr><td>16</td><td><code>triggers</code></td><td></td><td>Automation hooks (on_publish, on_enrollment, on_certificate_earn, etc.)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>17</td><td><code>discussion</code></td><td></td><td>GitHub Discussions configuration</td></tr>
          <tr><td>18</td><td><code>changelog</code></td><td>✓</td><td>Version history with dates and changes</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="sections" class="docs-section">
    <h2 class="docs-section-title">Key YAML Sections Reference</h2>

    <h3 style="font-size:0.95rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--text-primary);margin:1.25rem 0 0.5rem">metadata</h3>
    <div class="docs-table-wrap">
      <table class="docs-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Req</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>id</code></td><td>string</td><td>✓</td><td>Kebab-case, globally unique. <strong>Permanent — never change after publish.</strong></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>version</code></td><td>semver</td><td>✓</td><td>Bump on breaking curriculum changes.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>schema_version</code></td><td>string</td><td>✓</td><td>Always <code>"3.0"</code> — do not change.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>status</code></td><td>enum</td><td>✓</td><td><code>draft</code> <code>review</code> <code>published</code> <code>archived</code> <code>deprecated</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>visibility</code></td><td>enum</td><td>✓</td><td><code>public</code> <code>unlisted</code> <code>private</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>language</code></td><td>string</td><td>✓</td><td>ISO 639-1 code, e.g. <code>en</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>solutions_file</code></td><td>path</td><td>✓</td><td>Always <code>solutions.yaml</code> — the companion file with all answers.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h3 style="font-size:0.95rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--text-primary);margin:1.25rem 0 0.5rem">classification — Track slugs</h3>
    <p>The <code>category</code> field must be one of the 12 valid track slugs:</p>
    <div class="docs-table-wrap">
      <table class="docs-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Slug</th><th>Track Name</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>foundations</code></td><td>Foundations &amp; Theory</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>languages</code></td><td>Languages &amp; Paradigms</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>web</code></td><td>Web &amp; Mobile</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>backend</code></td><td>Backend &amp; Databases</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>systems</code></td><td>Systems &amp; Infrastructure</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>networks</code></td><td>Networks &amp; Protocols</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>data</code></td><td>Data &amp; AI</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>security</code></td><td>Security &amp; Cryptography</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>architecture</code></td><td>Architecture &amp; Engineering</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>creative</code></td><td>Creative Computing</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>emerging</code></td><td>Emerging Technologies</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>applied</code></td><td>Applied &amp; Cross-Domain</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h3 style="font-size:0.95rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--text-primary);margin:1.25rem 0 0.5rem">curriculum — Content node hierarchy</h3>
    <p>Lessons are the leaf nodes. The hierarchy is flexible — flatten any level if not needed:</p>
    <div class="docs-pre">
      <div class="docs-pre__bar"><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__lang">yaml</span></div>
      <code>curriculum:
  chapters:
    - id: ch-01
      title: "Chapter 1 Title"
      chapter_test_id: ctest-ch-01         # required — links to chapter_tests[]
      chapter_assignment_id: cassign-ch-01  # optional — links to chapter_assignments[]
      sections:
        - id: ch-01-s-01
          title: "Section Title"
          subsections:
            - id: ch-01-s-01-sub-01
              title: "Subsection Title"
              lessons:
                - id: ch-01-s-01-sub-01-l-01
                  title: "Lesson Title"
                  type: video       # video|reading|code|exercise|reference|project
                  duration_minutes: 15
                  free_preview: true
                  content:
                    video:
                      url: "https://youtube.com/watch?v=..."
                      credit_id: src-01  # references credits[] by id
                    text:
                      format: markdown
                      body: |
                        ## Watch Guide
                        Notes and context...</code>
    </div>

    <h3 style="font-size:0.95rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--text-primary);margin:1.25rem 0 0.5rem">chapter_tests — Question bank (answers in solutions.yaml)</h3>
    <div class="docs-pre">
      <div class="docs-pre__bar"><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__lang">yaml</span></div>
      <code>chapter_tests:
  - id: ctest-ch-01
    attached_to: ch-01
    gates_next_chapter: true
    passing_score: 70
    max_attempts: 3
    time_limit_minutes: 30
    randomize_questions: true
    show_answers_after: passed      # passed | attempted | never
    sections:
      - id: ctest-ch-01-s-01
        title: "Conceptual Understanding"
        weight: 50                  # percentage of total score
        questions:
          - id: ctest-ch-01-s-01-q-01
            type: mcq
            points: 10
            difficulty: easy
            topic: variables
            question: "Question text?"
            options: ["A", "B", "C", "D"]
            # answer: see solutions.yaml → ctest-ch-01-s-01-q-01</code>
    </div>
    <div class="docs-callout docs-callout--warn">
      <span class="docs-callout__icon">⚠️</span>
      <div class="docs-callout__body"><strong>No answers in <code>course.yaml</code>.</strong> Questions are in <code>course.yaml</code>; answers and explanations are in the private <code>solutions.yaml</code>. Reference them via <code>question_id</code>.</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="questions" class="docs-section">
    <h2 class="docs-section-title">Question Types</h2>
    <p>All question types are supported in <code>chapter_tests[].sections[].questions[]</code> and <code>final_test.sections[].questions[]</code>:</p>
    <div class="docs-table-wrap">
      <table class="docs-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Type</th><th>Required fields</th><th>Grading</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>mcq</code></td><td><code>options: string[]</code></td><td>Exact match on index. Auto.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>multi</code></td><td><code>options: string[]</code></td><td>Partial credit: correct_selected / total_correct × points. Auto.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>truefalse</code></td><td>—</td><td>Exact bool match. Auto.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>short</code></td><td><code>keywords: string[]</code></td><td>Keyword match. <code>grading: keywords</code>. Partial credit per matched keyword.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>code_output</code></td><td><code>code.snippet</code>, <code>options: string[]</code></td><td>"What does this code log?" — exact option match. Auto.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>code_fix</code></td><td><code>code.snippet</code>, <code>grading</code></td><td>Fix the bug. <code>grading: diff</code> or <code>manual</code>.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>code_write</code></td><td><code>language</code>, <code>starter</code>, <code>grading</code></td><td>Write from scratch. <code>grading: manual</code> — maintainer reviews.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>code_reading</code></td><td><code>code.snippet</code>, <code>options: string[]</code></td><td>Read and analyse code. Exact option match. Auto.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <div class="docs-callout docs-callout--info">
      <span class="docs-callout__icon">ℹ️</span>
      <div class="docs-callout__body">Short-answer questions use keyword matching — no AI, no semantic analysis. List at least 3 distinct keywords per question. Grading is purely deterministic: keyword presence counts, case-insensitive.</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="solutions" class="docs-section">
    <h2 class="docs-section-title">solutions.yaml — The Private Companion</h2>
    <p><code>solutions.yaml</code> lives in the same directory as <code>course.yaml</code>. It contains all answers, explanations, and grading rubrics. It <strong>must never be committed to the main branch</strong>.</p>

    <div class="docs-pre">
      <div class="docs-pre__bar"><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__lang">yaml</span></div>
      <code>course_id: your-course-slug
visibility: private
maintainer: manojpisini

solutions:

  # MCQ: answer is the 0-indexed option (0=A, 1=B, 2=C, 3=D)
  - question_id: ctest-ch-01-s-01-q-01
    type: mcq
    answer: 1
    explanation: "Option B is correct because..."
    points: 10

  # True/False
  - question_id: ctest-ch-01-s-01-q-02
    type: truefalse
    answer: true
    explanation: "This is true because..."
    points: 5

  # Multi: array of 0-indexed correct options
  - question_id: ctest-ch-01-s-01-q-03
    type: multi
    answers: [0, 1, 3]
    explanation: "Options A, B, D are correct because..."
    points: 15

  # Short: sample answer for reference; grading uses keywords from course.yaml
  - question_id: ctest-ch-01-s-02-q-01
    type: short
    sample_answer: "A closure is a function that..."
    explanation: "Full explanation..."
    points: 20

  # Code fix: the correct code
  - question_id: ctest-ch-01-s-02-q-02
    type: code_fix
    correct_code: |
      for (let i = 0; i &lt; 3; i++) &#123;
        setTimeout(() =&gt; console.log(i), 0);
      &#125;
    bugs_fixed:
      - "Changed var to let — creates a new binding per iteration"
    explanation: "..."
    points: 25

  # Code write: sample solution + grading rubric
  - question_id: ft-s-02-q-01
    type: code_write
    sample_solution: |
      async function fetchAll(urls) &#123;
        return Promise.all(urls.map(url =&gt;
          fetch(url).then(r =&gt; r.json()).catch(() =&gt; null)
        ));
      &#125;
    grading_rubric:
      - criterion: "Returns array same length as urls"
        points: 10
      - criterion: "Failed requests return null"
        points: 15
      - criterion: "Requests run in parallel"
        points: 10
    points: 35

assignment_review_guides:
  - assignment_id: cassign-ch-01
    what_to_look_for:
      - All functions are pure (no side effects)
      - Tests present and passing
    common_mistakes:
      - Using Math.random() inside a pure function
    pass_threshold: 60</code>
    </div>
    <div class="docs-callout docs-callout--danger">
      <span class="docs-callout__icon">🔒</span>
      <div class="docs-callout__body">Add <code>solutions.yaml</code> to <code>.gitignore</code> before your first commit. The grader accesses it at runtime from a secure private location — it is never served publicly.</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="assets" class="docs-section">
    <h2 class="docs-section-title">Assets</h2>
    <div class="docs-table-wrap">
      <table class="docs-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Directory</th><th>Contents</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>assets/images/</code></td><td>thumbnail, banner, og image, badge</td><td>thumbnail 16:9 min 800×450px · banner 3:1 min 1200×400px · og 1200×630px · badge square</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>assets/code/</code></td><td>Runnable code examples</td><td>Organised by chapter: <code>code/ch01/example.js</code>. Referenced in lesson <code>code_blocks[].file</code>.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>assets/docs/</code></td><td>PDFs, cheatsheets, assignment briefs</td><td>Referenced in lesson <code>files[]</code> and assignment <code>content.files[]</code>.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <div class="docs-callout docs-callout--tip">
      <span class="docs-callout__icon">💡</span>
      <div class="docs-callout__body">There is no <code>tests/</code> or <code>starter/</code> directory in the new format. Dynamic test generators go inside <code>chapter_tests</code> questions directly. Starter repos are linked via <code>lesson.content.exercise.starter_repo</code>.</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="pr-workflow" class="docs-section">
    <h2 class="docs-section-title">PR Workflow</h2>
    <div class="docs-steps" style="--ch-color:#a78bfa">
      <div class="docs-step">
        <div class="docs-step__line"><div class="docs-step__num">1</div><div class="docs-step__connector"></div></div>
        <div class="docs-step__body">
          <p class="docs-step__title">Create a branch and copy the template</p>
          <p class="docs-step__desc"><code>git checkout -b course/your-slug</code> then <code>cp -r engine/courses/template engine/courses/your-slug</code></p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="docs-step">
        <div class="docs-step__line"><div class="docs-step__num">2</div><div class="docs-step__connector"></div></div>
        <div class="docs-step__body">
          <p class="docs-step__title">Edit course.yaml and add assets</p>
          <p class="docs-step__desc">Fill in all 18 sections. Write lessons and tests in YAML. Add images, code files, and docs to <code>assets/</code>. Keep <code>solutions.yaml</code> gitignored — never push to main.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="docs-step">
        <div class="docs-step__line"><div class="docs-step__num">3</div><div class="docs-step__connector"></div></div>
        <div class="docs-step__body">
          <p class="docs-step__title">Open a PR → validate-pr.yml runs</p>
          <p class="docs-step__desc">Automatically parses <code>course.yaml</code>, validates all required fields, checks for engine path tampering, and posts a validation report as a PR comment.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="docs-step">
        <div class="docs-step__line"><div class="docs-step__num">4</div><div class="docs-step__connector"></div></div>
        <div class="docs-step__body">
          <p class="docs-step__title">Merge → automated publish</p>
          <p class="docs-step__desc"><code>course-publish.yml</code> generates <code>course.json</code> + <code>contributors.json</code>. <code>sync-site-data.yml</code> aggregates. <code>deploy-site.yml</code> rebuilds. Live in ~90 seconds.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="docs-callout docs-callout--danger">
      <span class="docs-callout__icon">🔒</span>
      <div class="docs-callout__body">The <code>id</code> in <code>metadata.id</code> is permanent once published. Changing it invalidates all existing enrollment issues for that course. Add old IDs to <code>metadata.slug_aliases</code> if you must rename.</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="checklist" class="docs-section">
    <h2 class="docs-section-title">Course Creator Checklist</h2>
    <ul class="docs-checklist">
      <li><code>metadata.id</code> is lowercase-hyphen and globally unique</li>
      <li><code>metadata.status</code> is <code>draft</code> initially — change to <code>review</code> when ready for merge</li>
      <li><code>identity.description.short</code> is under 200 characters</li>
      <li><code>classification.category</code> is one of the 12 valid track slugs</li>
      <li>All <code>credits[].id</code> values are unique and referenced via <code>credit_id</code> in lessons</li>
      <li><code>prerequisites.courses</code> references only valid, published course IDs</li>
      <li>Every chapter has a <code>chapter_test_id</code> that matches an entry in <code>chapter_tests[]</code></li>
      <li>Chapter test section weights sum to 100 per test</li>
      <li>Each chapter test has at least 3 questions</li>
      <li><code>passing_score</code> is 50–90 on all tests and assignments</li>
      <li>Short-answer questions have at least 3 keywords; answers in <code>solutions.yaml</code></li>
      <li><code>solutions.yaml</code> is in <code>.gitignore</code> — never committed to main</li>
      <li>Banner image is at least 1200×400px (3:1 ratio)</li>
      <li><code>people.curator.github</code> is set</li>
      <li><code>effort.total_hours</code> is realistic</li>
      <li><code>certificate.requirements</code> references valid test/assignment IDs</li>
      <li><code>changelog</code> has at least one entry</li>
      <li>YAML validated locally before opening the PR</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
